properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 18 at 12:16PM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Blizzard Conditions Continue Across Northern Iowa Today...

.Potent northwest winds gusting to 45 to 50 mph will continue
to cause blizzard conditions with widespread blowing and drifting
snow across northern Iowa today. Whiteout conditions can be
expected at times, especially in rural areas. Further south across
central and southern Iowa, areas of blowing and drifting snow
will still make travel difficult at times in rural areas due to
the gusty northwest winds. Dangerously cold wind chill values well
below zero are likely by late this afternoon and evening.

* WHAT...Areas of blowing and drifting snow, especially in rural
areas. Winds gusting as high as 45 mph.

* WHERE...West central and central Iowa.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Difficult travel conditions expected especially in
rural areas due to reduced visibilities in blowing snow, and
slick spots on roads due to drifting snow across roadways.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
